      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LITTLE VESPER (4) was sent out long odds last time but charged out of the boxes with a strong early sectional and went on to clock 29.66 in a 2.25 lengths win at this track over 520m. Speedy beginner who can find the front with a clean break from the middle of the draw. Can make it two on the bounce. VIN ROSE (3) is better than last start when eighth (30.78) in a OPEN at Q Parklands over 520m. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Cannot be taken lightly. RADIANT ETHICS (1) has a moderate overall strike-rate. Better run when finding the frame last time though, finishing third (25.38) at Maitland. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Expected to be in this for a long way. DONE DEALING (2) is in the mix despite finishing out of the placings here last start.",
